// Issue #13 — labeled queries fixture for `benches/quant_sweep.rs`.
//
// Format: one JSON object per line, matching `eval_ndcg::LabeledQuery`:
//   { "query": "<free-text>", "relevant_ids": ["<session-uuid>", ...] }
//
// Comment lines (`#` or `//`) and blank lines are skipped by the bench
// loader. `relevant_ids` are listed in descending relevance order (most
// relevant first); nDCG@10 counts each id found in the top-10 results,
// discounted by rank.
//
// These rows are matched to the `examples/sample-corpus/` fixture
// committed alongside the bench harness. Each query is a paraphrase or
// related keyword for one (or more) of the 12 sessions — see
// `examples/sample-corpus/README.md` for the full session map.
//
// To author new entries for your own corpus, run `memex scan ~/.claude/projects`
// to list session_ids, pick queries that should match each, and add one
// JSON line per query.

